ivardefs.name: approvalDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was approved by the publisher. Approval happens once when the content is officially approved for usage.

ivardefs.name: assertion
ivardefs.desc: Declarative description of the Evidence.

ivardefs.name: certainty_
ivardefs.desc: Level of certainty.

ivardefs.name: contributor_
ivardefs.desc: Contact detail and role for contributor to summary.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the summary was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the summary changes.

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the evidence from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: distribution_
ivardefs.desc: Ordered distribution.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this summary when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: lastReviewDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was last reviewed. Review happens periodically after approval but does not change the original approval date.

ivardefs.name: note_
ivardefs.desc: Footnotes and/or explanatory notes.

ivardefs.name: referentGroup
ivardefs.desc: Group being referenced.

ivardefs.name: relatedArtifact_
ivardefs.desc: Link or citation to artifact associated with the summary.

ivardefs.name: statistic_
ivardefs.desc: The statistic value(s).

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this summary. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: studyType
ivardefs.desc: The type of study that produced this summary.

ivardefs.name: synthesisType
ivardefs.desc: The particular type of synthesis if this is a synthesis summary.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the summary.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this evidence when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance; also called its canonical identifier. This SHOULD be globally unique and SHOULD be a literal address at which at which an author

ivardefs.name: useContext_

ivardefs.name: variableDefinition_
ivardefs.desc: Evidence variable.

ivardefs.name: version

properties.desc: This represents statistics, certainty, both the intended and actual population, and evidence variables.
